Claims What is claimed is: 1. A method, comprising: receiving from a first ciient device, in relation to a command to create an image comment on a first image in a collaborative content item, an image identifier for the first image, image comment, and an indication of a portion of the first image with which the image comment is associated; storing relative coordinates stored in association with a record of the image identifier and the image comment, wherein the relative coordinates define the indicated portion of a the first image relative to dimensions of the first image; causing a second client device to display the collaborative content item including the first image and the image comment; causing the second ciient device to display a tag at a portion of the first image based on the relative coordinates of the image comment and dimensions of the first image, the tag identifying the image comment; receiving from the second client an image identifier for a second image to replace the first image; causing the client device to display the collaborative content item including the second image and the image comment: and causing the client device to display the tag at a portion of the second image based on the relative coordinates of the image comment and dimensions of the second image. 2. The method of claim i, wherein receiving a command to create an image comment on a first image in a collaborative content item, further comprises: receiving, from the client device, a selection of a user interface element displayed in conjunction with the comment to create an image comment. 3. The method of claim 1, wherein receiving an indication of a portion of the first image with which the image comment is associated, further comprises: receiving from the client device a selection of a single location in the first image to associate with the image comment: and 4. The method of claim 1 , wherein receiving an indication of a portion of the first image with which the image comment is associated further comprises: receiving from the client device a selection of a bounding area in the first image to associated with the image comment. 5. The method of claim 1, wherein causing the second client device to display a tag at a portion of the first image comprises: determining whether the relative coordinates are within a threshold distance of a portion of the first image associated with a previously created image comment; and responsive to the relative coordinates being within the threshold distance, creating a tag cluster indicating both the tag and the previously created tag; and displaying the tag cluster at a portion of the second image based on the relative coordinates of the image comment and relative coordinates of the previously created image comment. 6. The method of claim 1, wherein causing the client device to display the tag at a portion of the second image based on the relative coordinates of the image comment and dimensions of the second image further comprises: determining an amount by which the second image is cropped from the first image; adjusting the relative coordinates of the image comment based on the amount by which the second image is cropped from the first image; displaying the tag at the portion of the second image based on the adjusted relative coordinates of the image comment and the dimensions of the second image. 7. The method of claim 1, wherein dimensions of the first image comprise a horizontal and dimension and a vertical dimension, and the relative coordinates comprises a percentage of the first image in the horizontal dimension and a percentage of the first image in the vertical dimension, 8. The method of claim 7, wherein causing the client device to display the tag at a portion of the second image based on the relative coordinates of the image comment and dimensions of the second image comprises causes multiplying the percentage of the first image in the horizontal dimension by a horizontal dimension of the second 